# Project: Gander (working name)

## What it is
A location-based dating app for gay men — users discover and connect with nearby people, view profiles, and message in real time.

## Goals
**North star:** A new user near other users can go from app open → first sent message in one session, and come back the next day.

**v1 success criteria (measurable):**
- Growth: steady week-over-week signup growth; >60% of signups complete profile + age verification.
- Activation: >40% of new users send a message within their first session.
- Engagement: D1 retention >35%, D7 >20%; median active user opens the app ≥3 days/week.
- Safety floor (gates everything above): location provably non-trilaterable in pen test; reports actioned <24h. Growth never ships at the cost of these — see Non-negotiables.

Non-goals for v1 are covered under **Out of scope** — don't relitigate scope to chase a metric.

## Users
Primary: gay men (18+) looking to meet, date, or connect locally. Broad audience — both casual and relationship-focused; no narrower niche in v1.

## Core loop
Open app → browse distance-sorted grid of nearby users → open a profile → like/message → chat.

## Platforms
iOS + Android from a single codebase. No web app for v1.
