## MVP features
- Account creation + auth
- Profile (photos, bio, attributes)
- Location-based discovery — **distance-sorted browse grid** (Grindr-style), with basic filters
- Likes / favorites
- Real-time 1:1 messaging — text + images, typing indicators, read receipts (no voice/video in v1)
- Blocking + reporting
- Age gate (18+) + third-party identity/photo verification

## Non-negotiables — safety & privacy (architectural constraints, NOT features to bolt on later)
- **Never expose exact location.** Coordinates are fuzzed/snapped server-side; the client only ever receives coarse distance, and precision is capped to prevent trilateration (a real, documented attack against apps in this category).
- Let users hide distance / show approximate area only.
- Treat the user database as high-sensitivity. For this audience, an outing is a safety incident — including in regions where being gay is criminalized. Encrypt at rest, minimize retention, least-privilege access.
- Mandatory 18+ age verification.
- Strong moderation: one-tap reporting, instant blocking, an abuse-review pipeline.
- Photo / identity verification to reduce catfishing and bad actors — via third-party KYC/age vendor (e.g. Persona, Veriff, Yoti), not built in-house.

## Launch markets
v1: US + Western Europe. Threat model is designed as if hostile/criminalized regions are in scope eventually — security bar assumes state-level adversaries, even where we don't launch first. Drives GDPR compliance, data-residency choices, and age-verification law.

## Monetization
Freemium: free core + premium subscription. Paywalled in v1: who-liked-you, incognito / hide-distance browsing, extended reach (see more / further profiles), advanced filters. Core discovery + messaging stay free.

## Scale, budget, timeline (assumption — veto if wrong)
Solo founder / tiny team shipping to real users. Lean MVP, ~3-month target to v1. Managed-services-first to maximize speed and minimize ops; optimize the geo and infra layers only when usage demands it.

## Out of scope for v1
Voice/video chat, web app, events or group features, profile albums / private-photo sharing, advanced matching algorithms, in-app purchases beyond the single premium subscription.

## Tech stack
Managed-services-first. Locked for v1:
- **Client:** React Native + Expo — one codebase (iOS + Android), OTA updates, Expo Push for notifications.
- **Backend:** Supabase — Postgres (with **PostGIS** for geo), **Row Level Security** for the high-sensitivity user DB, Realtime for messaging, Auth (email + Apple/Google sign-in), Storage for photos, Edge Functions for webhooks/secret-holding work.
- **Geo fuzzing:** PostGIS + server-side RPCs snap/round coordinates; client only ever receives coarse distance. Enforces the location non-negotiable.
- **Age/identity verification:** third-party KYC vendor (Persona or Veriff — decide at verification phase). Not built in-house.

Rationale: RLS + PostGIS give provable least-privilege access and real server-side geo math — the right primitives for this threat model — in one managed platform a solo founder can run. Chosen over Firebase (weaker geo + access-control fit) and roll-your-own (too much ops).

Known later-optimization: Supabase Realtime is fine for v1 messaging scale; revisit only if chat volume demands it.
